# Privacy Policy for Sudoku Academy

**Last updated: July 2026**

Sudoku Academy is developed and published by me. This Privacy Policy explains what information the App collects, how it is used, and the choices you have.

## Summary

Sudoku Academy works fully offline by default. All of your game progress, statistics, and puzzle library stay on your device — we never see them. Two optional features involve Google's own services: signing in with Google Play Games (for achievements and a leaderboard), and a one-time Premium purchase.

## Information We Collect

### Data stored only on your device
By default, all of your game data stays on your device and is never sent to us or anyone else — including your game progress, saved and paused rounds, statistics and completion history, your Puzzle Library (custom, imported, and scanned puzzles), and app settings (theme, sound, language, etc.). This is true whether or not you sign in — signing in does not currently back up or sync this data anywhere; it stays local to each device.

We have no access to this data and cannot retrieve it if you uninstall the App or clear its storage.

### Optional Google Sign-In (achievements & leaderboard)
The App offers an optional "Sign in with Google Play Games" feature, available in Settings. This is never required to play — every difficulty, variant, and Strategy Academy lesson works fully without it.

If you choose to sign in, Google Play Games Services shares with us your Google Play Games player ID and public display name, so we can record which achievements you've unlocked and your score on the puzzle-count leaderboard through Google's own systems. We do not receive your Google account password, email address, or any data from other apps.

The leaderboard shows a running total of puzzles you've solved. Your display name and score on it may be visible to other players who also use Google Play Games. You can manage or revoke the App's access to your Google Play Games account at any time through your Google Account settings.

### Camera / Physical Board Scanning (Beta)
The App includes an optional feature that lets you take a photo of a printed Sudoku puzzle to digitize it. This photo is processed entirely on your device — it is never uploaded to us or to any server. The only network activity involved is a one-time download of an open-source text-recognition library (Tesseract.js) from a public content delivery network (CDN), which does not receive any of your personal data or photos.

### In-App Purchase (Premium / Pro)
The App offers an optional one-time purchase ("Premium" or "Pro") that unlocks additional features (such as the Auto-Solver and Puzzle Library, including physical board scanning). Purchases are processed entirely by Google Play Billing. We do not receive or store your payment card details or billing address — Google handles payment information according to its own privacy policy, available at https://policies.google.com/privacy. We only receive confirmation that a purchase was completed, so the App can unlock the corresponding features on your device.

## Data We Do Not Collect

We do not collect advertising identifiers, and the App does not display third-party ads. We do not use analytics or tracking SDKs. We do not currently back up or sync your game progress to any server, signed in or not.

## Children's Privacy

Sudoku Academy is intended for players aged 16 and up and is not directed at younger children. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe a child has provided us with personal information (for example, through a signed-in Google account), please contact us so we can address it.

## Data Security

Locally stored data is protected by your device's own operating system security. Where the App interacts with Google services (Sign-In, Play Games Services, Play Billing), those services are protected by Google's own security practices.

## Third-Party Services

The App uses the following third-party services, each governed by its own privacy policy:
- **Google Play Games Services** (optional sign-in, achievements, leaderboard) — https://policies.google.com/privacy
- **Google Play Billing** (one-time Premium purchase) — https://policies.google.com/privacy
- **jsDelivr CDN** (delivers the open-source OCR library used only for the on-device board-scanning feature) — https://www.jsdelivr.com/terms/privacy-policy-jsdelivr-net

## Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time — for example, if we add cloud saving, daily challenges, or other new features. Changes will be posted at this same location with an updated "Last updated" date. Continued use of the App after a change means you accept the updated policy.

